AU  - Kumar, Praveen
T1  - Strategic Ownership Structure and the Cost of Debt
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs062
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 7
SP  - 2257
EP  - 2299
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We theoretically and empirically address the endogeneity of corporate ownership structure and the cost of debt, with a novel emphasis on the role of control concentration in post-default firm restructuring. Control concentration raises agency costs of debt, and dominant shareholders trade off private benefits of control against higher borrowing costs in choosing their ownership stakes. Based on our theoretical predictions, and using an international sample of syndicated loans and unique dynamic ownership structure data, we present new evidence on the firm- and macro-level determinants of corporate control concentration and the cost of debt.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs062
ER  - 



